The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, April 24: The Reserve Bank of India has extended the period for final realisation of bad assets from five to seven years to abate the pressure of NPAs mounting on firms. The RBI had received representations from many asset reconstruction and securitisation companies, which had not been able to realise the financial assets acquired within the given time frame.                            
	 Mumbai, April 24: The sensex today gained 194 points to end at more than a six-month high of 11,329.05 on strong cues in European markets, which were higher by more than one per cent in early trade. The Asian indices closed with mixed results.                            
	 Seattle, April 24: Microsofts sales fell 6 per cent to $13.65 billion, marking the first year-on-year decline in quarterly revenue in its 34-year history. The companys quarterly profit fell, but its shares rose as investors welcomed cost-cutting efforts and news that the release of Windows 7 was on track.                            
	 New Delhi, April 24: Tech Mahindra has advised Satyam shareholders to wait till June 22 for the final price before tendering their shares, hinting at a possible increase in the price.                            
	 New Delhi, April 24: The Central Board of Direct Taxes has extended the time period for availing higher depreciation benefit on commercial vehicles by six months up to September-end.                                                                                                                           
